reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This bag is so much better quality than I expected! It arrived, wrapped and packaged so thoughtfully. It came with a dust bag to place it in when not in use. But it's very large, plenty of space to fit everything I need for the office. There are so many thoughtful details including the multiple electronics pockets, elastic pockets on the inside for water bottles, an attached hook for your keys so you don't lose them in the bag, a wonderfully sized cosmetic bag that can be used for cords, makeup, pens, etc. It has metal feet on the bottom to keep the bottom of the bag off the floor and clean. The removable strap to wear crossbody or even just longer is comfortable and thick and incredible quality. The bag is sturdy, thick, and just gorgeous. A clean and classic look. I am obsessed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Wanted to love it but a little impractical
reviews.reviewText: I really liked this bag but it just didn't do it for me and I had to return. It's way bigger than you'd expect but oddly can't fit much. The center zipper for laptops/tablets is in such a weird place. Since it goes through the middle of the bag you have the main section cut into two and can't really fit things in either side. I ended up having to bring another tote to work with me to hold things like my lunch, jacket, water bottle.As other reviews said, it gets really heavy. I didn't even put too much in it and it was pretty heavy compared to a normal bag/backpack with the same things inside (I think because of the material of it). I wanted a bag that could stay more organized but the slip pocked and zippers are a little useless and you just end up trying to fit most things in those two main compartments. The Canvas also gets dirty quickly (picks up pet hair, lint, etc.) so keep that in mind when choosing a color!However, it's really cute and seems like decent quality for a great price. It gives you a designer feel for under $50. The straps are comfortable/sturdy and the feet on the bottom are a plus to keep the bag clean/undamaged wherever you put it. The little bag that it comes with is great because it's actually a decent size to use as a small handbag or if you want necessities/your wallet in there for on the go. For me, I just didn't like the organization of it but wouldn't discourage others from buying it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is a good professional bag. It fits my 15” laptop, keyboard, mouse, wallet, keys, phone and everything else from my purse. It’s very spacious and has a good amount of pockets on the inside. Also has a key leash which is nice. Very professional and chic looking for the price. I’ve received many compliments on it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was blown away by the quality of this bag ! More than happy with it. I was back and forth with purchasing it and finally took the chance.It it’s definitely big enough! I could probably fit double of everything in it.Bonus points for the pouch it comes with too! The pouch even has sections in itOne of my favorite purchases. Not one complaint !

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Decent outside, good pocket placement, but poor inside material quality
reviews.reviewText: I did much searching for a new shoulder bag that’d be cute and functional to take to work and also work to take on the weekends to run errands. I wanted a bag that things couldn’t get “lost” in and would be easy to find. This bag checked the boxes, but when I received it I wasn’t overly impressed. It had a cute small matching bag for maybe makeup/toiletries and the placement of pockets inside was great. Quality of the outside was good, but the inside material was a disappointment, seemed cheap. I couldn’t get past it and will be returning it. I even felt the zipper quality was poor and the length/placement of the top zipper was funny. Super long on one end where you need to tuck it into the bag and then it doesn’t zip all the way to cover the top of the bag. Could use some improvements then would be a 5/5 star bag to me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I really like this bag for taking to the office. It’s got a great slot for a laptop. Mine is 15.6 inches and fits well. I also really appreciate the pouch that comes with the bag as well. If you’re a fan of multiple sections and pockets in a bag, you will love this! Delivery wasn’t as long as I thought it would be which was nice. It is quite big and can feel quite heavy with a laptop in but that could also depend on how heavy your laptop is. Would recommend this if you’re looking for a new work bag
